# .gitignore
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security-hardening baseline for the net-new Node.js/Express application.
#
# Purpose: guarantee that installed dependencies, local environment files, and
# TLS/cryptographic material NEVER enter version control. This directly
# enforces the "No secrets in version control" requirement of the security
# hardening plan (AAP Sections 0.6.1, 0.9.1, and 0.11.2).
#
# Format: plain text, one pattern per line; comments are prefixed with '#'.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Node.js dependencies
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Installed packages are restored deterministically from the committed
# package-lock.json via `npm ci`, so the tree itself is never committed.
# NOTE: package-lock.json is intentionally NOT ignored — it must be committed
# for reproducible, auditable installs (`npm ci` / `npm audit`).
node_modules/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Environment files (secrets / local configuration)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Never commit real secrets or machine-local configuration. The broad
# `.env.*` rule catches every local variant (e.g. .env.local, .env.production,
# .env.development.local). The secret-free template `.env.example` IS part of
# the repository, so it is explicitly re-included via the negation below.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TLS / cryptographic material (HTTPS keys and certificates)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Private keys and certificates are provisioned out-of-band at deploy time
# (paths supplied via TLS_KEY_PATH / TLS_CERT_PATH) and must never be stored
# in the repository.
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.cert
/certs
/certs/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Logs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
npm-debug.log*
logs/
*.log

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test coverage reports (jest)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
coverage/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS / editor cruft
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
